<paragraph blockId="26.[142,758,362,537]" box="[142,251,362,383]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis box="[142,251,362,383]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[142,758,362,537]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">By endoantennal conglobation ability and simple coxal plates. Eyes represented by dark pigment, but no lenses are visible. In dorsal view, the visible portion of the uropod sympodite is nearly twice as wide as long. Pleotelson with median shallow tubercle.</paragraph>
